850#Concussion # History
	('850#Concussion', 'WAS_FIRST_DESCRIBED_BY', 'Muhammad ibn Zakarīya Rāzi')
	('850#Concussion', 'WAS_DESCRIBED_AS', 'transient loss of function with no physical damage')
	('850#Concussion', 'HAS_HISTORY', 'in the 10th century')
	('850#Concussion', 'WAS_DISTINGUISHED_FROM', 'other types of head injury')
	('850#Concussion', 'WAS_DESCRIBED_AS', 'brain "commotion"')
	('850#Concussion', 'HAD_GOOD_PROGNOSIS', 'compared to more severe types of head trauma')
	('850#Concussion', 'CAME_ INTO _USE', 'in the 16th century')
	('850#Concussion', 'WAS_DESCRIBED_AS', 'confusion, lethargy, and memory problems')
	('850#Concussion', 'WAS_EXPLORED_BY', 'more physicians after the invention of the microscope')
	('850#Concussion', 'WAS_NOT_THOUGHT_ TO_BE_FROM_PHYSICAL_DAMAGE', 'until the 17th century')
	('850#Concussion', 'WAS_DESCRIBED_AS', 'unconsciousness and other functional problems')
	('850#Concussion', 'WAS_DIFFERENTIATED_FROM', 'brain contusions')

007.0#Balantidiasis # Transmission
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_ACQUIRED_FROM', 'Fecally Contaminated Food and Water')
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_ZOONOTIC', 'Pig')

007.0#Balantidiasis # Morphology
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_CHARACTERIZED_BY', 'Large Size')
	('Balantidiasis', 'HAS_DEVELOPMENTAL_STAGES', 'Trophozoite and Cyst')
	('Balantidiasis', 'INFECTIVE_FORM', 'Trophozoite')
	('Balantidiasis', 'NOT_INFECTIVE_FORM', 'Cyst')
	('Balantidiasis', 'REPRODUCES_BY', 'Transverse Binary Fission')
	('Balantidiasis', 'HAS_MICRONUCLEUS', 'Less Prominent')
	('Balantidiasis', 'HAS_MACRONUCLEUS', 'Large and Sausage-Shaped')

	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_DIAGNOSED_BY', 'Microscopic Examination of Stools')
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_DIAGNOSED_BY', 'Colonoscopy or Sigmoidoscopy')
	('Balantidiasis', 'HAS_SYMPTOM', 'Diarrhea')
	('Balantidiasis', 'HAS_EXPOSURE', 'Contact with Infected Persons')
	('Balantidiasis', 'HAS_EXPOSURE', 'Anal Sexual Contact')

	('Balantidiasis', 'PREVENTED_BY', 'Personal and Community Hygiene')
	('Balantidiasis', 'PREVENTED_BY', 'Purification of Drinking Water')
	('Balantidiasis', 'PREVENTED_BY', 'Proper Handling of Food')
	('Balantidiasis', 'PREVENTED_BY', 'Careful Disposal of Human Feces')
	('Balantidiasis', 'MONITORED_BY', 'Contacts of Balantidiasis Patients')

	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_TREATED_WITH', 'Tetracycline')
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_TREATED_WITH', 'Metronidazole')
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_TREATED_WITH', 'Iodoquinol')

007.0#Balantidiasis # History
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_CAUSED_BY', 'Experiment by Cassagrandi and Barnagallo in 1896')
	('Balantidiasis', 'HAS_HISTORY', 'First case reported in the Philippines in 1904')
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_DISTRIBUTED_IN', 'Worldwide but less than 1% of human population is infected')
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_HOSTED_BY', 'Pigs')
	('Balantidiasis', 'IS_HOSTED_BY', 'Rats')

	('Balantidiasis', 'CAN_BE_FOUND_IN', 'Order Carnivora')

020.0#Bubonic plague # Overview
	('Bubonic plague', 'IS_CAUSED_BY', 'Yersinia pestis')
	('Bubonic plague', 'HAS_SYMPTOMS', 'fever, headaches, and vomiting')
	('Bubonic plague', 'HAS_SYMPTOMS', 'acral necrosis and swollen lymph nodes')
	('Bubonic plague', 'MAY_BE_SPREAD_BY', 'infected fleas from small animals')
	('Bubonic plague', 'MAY_BE_DIAGNOSED_BY', 'finding the bacteria in the blood, sputum, or fluid from lymph nodes')
	('Bubonic plague', 'PREVENTION_METHOD', 'public health measures such as not handling dead animals in areas where plague is common')
	('Bubonic plague', 'TREATMENT_METHOD', 'several antibiotics including streptomycin, gentamicin, and doxycycline')
	('Bubonic plague', 'RISK_OF_DEATH', 'around 10% with treatment, 30% to 90% without treatment')

343.0#Diplegic # History of the term diplegia
	('Diplegic', 'IS_DEFINED_AS', 'Symmetrical Limb Paralysis')
	('Diplegic', 'WAS_FIRST_REFERENCED_BY', 'Sachs and Peterson in 1890')
	('Diplegic', 'WAS_USED_IN_CLINICAL_FIELD_TO_DESCRIBE', 'Patients with Symmetrical Limb Paralysis in 1955')
	('Diplegic', 'PRESENTED_AS_A_FORM_OF', 'Bilateral Cerebral Palsy Affecting Like Parts on Either Side of the Body in 1956')
	('Diplegic', 'DIFFERS_FROM', "Tetraplegia by Considering the Patient's Upper Limb's Ability to Express a Sufficient Support Reaction in 1965")

518.5#ARDS # History
	('ARDS', 'IS_DEFINED_AS', 'Acute Respiratory Distress Syndrome')
	('ARDS', 'WAS_FIRST_DESCRIBED_BY', 'Ashbaugh et al.')
	('ARDS', 'HAD_NO_CLEARLY_ESTABLISHED_DEFINITION', 'Initially')
	('ARDS', 'HAD_CONTROVERSY_REGARDING_INCIDENCE_AND_DEATH', 'Initially')
	('ARDS', 'HAD_AN_EXPANDED_DEFINITION_PROPOSED', '1988')
	('ARDS', 'HAD_A_NEW_DEFINITION_RECOMMENDED', '1994')
	('ARDS', 'REQUIRED_CRITERIA_FOR_DIAGNOSIS', 'acute onset, persistent dyspnea bilateral infiltrates on chest radiograph consistent with pulmonary edema hypoxemia')
	('ARDS', 'LIMITATIONS_OF_DEFINITIONS', 'lack of precise definition of acuity, nonspecific imaging criteria, lack of precise definition of hypoxemia with regards to PEEP')
	('ARDS', 'HAD_BERLIN_DEFINITION_DEVISED', '2012')
